title: Dashcam footage captures cyclist taking a painful tumble | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share Mr Moule said: 'He was bruised and battered but had no broken bones, his elbow hurt the most as that's what took most of the damage. 'It was his clothing and bike came out worse off. 'After about five minutes the driver came out of her car. A nurse was behind me and you can see her tending to him at the end of the video. The bike rider falls to the ground clutching his arm. He appears to be in pain but is able to stand Richard Moule was driving behind the pair and helped the cyclist up. The 23-year-old can be heard commenting how close the car is to the cyclist in dashcam footage moments before they connect The quality inspector said the police were called but no further legal action was taken. He said: 'Another driver in the blue Polo called an ambulance, I hovered around for about five minutes but I wasn't needed so I gave my details and left. 'I believe it's only being dealt with through insurances.' Share or comment on this article Most watched News videos
